snippet.textDisplay: There is a problem with what you said though. I have heard from various geologist professors that only a small few of scientists truly believe that humans evolved from apes. It just so happened that theory, when it came out back in the day, caused a lot of noise because everyone was under the assumption that God created us. In other words, people were very religious back then. Due to a small few scientists stating that we came from apes, it made other scientist look as though they believed in it as well. When in reality, some scientist thought that was preposterous. There are a variety of theories and supporting evidence for our origin. However, this one about the ape is only a small portion.
